@startuml
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam rectangleRoundCorner 8
skinparam rectangleFontSize 13
skinparam rectangleFontStyle bold

title The Allowed-to-Use Relation\nPermissions define valid dependencies; violations break the architecture

rectangle "Layer C\n**Presentation**" as C #B3D9FF
rectangle "Layer B\n**Business Logic**" as B #CCE5CC
rectangle "Layer A\n**Data Access**" as A #FFE0B2

C -[#339933]-> B : allowed
B -[#339933]-> A : allowed

C -[#CC9933,dashed]-> A : allowed\n//(relaxed only)//

A -[#CC3333]-> C : **VIOLATION**\n//upward dependency//

legend right
  | Arrow | Meaning |
  |<#339933> | Allowed dependency |
  |<#CC9933> ~~~ | Relaxed-only permission |
  |<#CC3333> | Architectural violation |
end legend

note bottom
  **Key properties:**
  * Defines permissions, not requirements
  * Transitivity depends on strict vs. relaxed rules
  * Violations indicate architectural erosion
end note
@enduml
